abstract.text: Provides the delegate the movie file URL resulting from a Live Photo capture.

inlineContent.text: The photo output performing the capture.
The file URL at which the movie content of the Live Photo was written.
The duration of the Live Photo movie.
The timestamp within the movie to which the still image part of the Live Photo corresponds.
An object describing the settings used for this capture. Match this object’s
value to the

property of the photo settings object you initiated capture with to determine which capture request this delegate call corresponds to. You can also use this object to find out which values the photo output has chosen for automatic settings.
If the capture process could not proceed successfully, an error object describing the failure; otherwise,
Use this method to receive the results of a Live Photo capture. When the photo output calls this method, the movie component of the Live Photo has been written to the location specified by the
parameter and the Live Photo is ready for consumption. (To receive the still image component of the Live Photo, implement the
method.)
To add captured Live Photos to the user’s Photos library, use the
class. To use Live Photos from the Photos library, use the
and
classes. To display Live Photo content on the web, use the
framework.
You don’t need to implement this method if you’re not requesting Live Photo capture.
You must implement this method if you request Live Photo capture (by setting the
property of your photo settings object). The photo output validates this requirement when you call its
method; if your delegate does not implement the correct methods, the photo output raises an exception.
The photo output calls this method only once for each Live Photo capture.

abstract.text: Work with audiovisual assets, control device cameras, process audio, and configure system audio interactions.
Methods for monitoring progress and receiving results from a photo capture output.
Tells the delegate when the system finishes capturing the photo proxy.
Provides the delegate the movie file URL resulting from a Live Photo capture.
Provides the delegate with the captured image and associated metadata resulting from a photo capture.
Provides the delegate a captured image in a processed format (such as JPEG).
Provides the delegate a captured image in RAW format.
Notifies the delegate that the movie content of a Live Photo has finished recording.
A capture output for still image, Live Photos, and other photography workflows.
Initiates a photo capture using the specified settings.
A URL at which to write Live Photo movie output.
A unique identifier for this photo settings instance.
A description of the features and settings in use for an in-progress or complete photo capture request.
Capture Live Photos like those created in the system Camera app and save them to the Photos library.
Monitor key events during capture to provide feedback in your camera UI.
Play Live Photos on the web.
A request to create a new Photos asset from underlying data resources, for use in a photo library change block.
A displayable representation of a Live Photo—a picture that includes motion and sound from the moments just before and after its capture.
A view that displays a Live Photo—a picture that also includes motion and sound from the moments just before and after its capture.
A structure that represents time.
Information about an error condition including a domain, a domain-specific error code, and application-specific information.
An object representing the location of a resource that bridges to ; use  when you need reference semantics or other Foundation-specific behavior.
A value that identifies the location of a resource, such as an item on a remote server or the path to a local file.
A type representing an error value that can be thrown.
